    "id": "f_csv_b0705e6f58",
    "slug": "i-don-t-understand-this-when-people-love-you-so-much-they-are-willing-to-get-ri",
    "texto": "I don't understand this--when people love you so much they are willing to get rid of you. I think if I loved someone that much I'd want to stay with them. It doesn't make sense that love would make a mother leave, and I wonder when this mother will love me that much too. I get the idea that love might be something to both desire and fear, and maybe if we don't love each other too much I won't have to go away again. I wonder why love works for everyone else, but it doesn't work for me.",
